narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Grading can be harsh and arbitrary. Cr/D recommended.

You learn how to write profiles, kind of, but really just explore different ways to explore writing about things. That's a little vague, which was a shortcoming of the class, but I recommend it. Professor Zarin's a great resource.

Be prepared to work hard in this class if you want to do well. It's a lot of writing, and the final profile, if you want to do a thorough and good job, requires a lot of planning. You start by writing about a natural object and work your way up to actually profiling a person in the conventional way. The assignments, on the whole, are inventive and fun.
A fun workshop that revolves around essays submitted every two weeks or so. Prof Zarin is an excellent, creative mind; it is worth taking the class in order to get to know her.
